# Workflow, documentation, and Isaac host rules

- At the start of every user turn, prepend the exact prompt to
  `docs/last_prompt.md` using `## BEGIN: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM ±HHMM` and `## END`.
  Move the prior current block under `# Old prompts:` without deleting history.
  Backfill omitted prompts from the same conversation when fixing the log.
- When changing behavior, configs, training, or verification, update in the
  same change set: `spec.md`, `README.md`, `REFERENCES.md`, `STATUS.md`,
  `CHANGES.md`, `docs/last_prompt.md`, and the applicable `docs/phaseN_*.md`.
- Summarize all changes in `CHANGES.md` and in the reply. Highlight items that
  need further review.
- Every new module or script gets a matching test under `tests/` (or
  `launch_testing` for ROS nodes). Python tests use `pytest`.
- Prefer host execution for Isaac Sim / Isaac Lab
  (`scripts/host/launch_isaac_sim.sh`, `scripts/host/spark_host_exec.sh`).
  The Isaac ROS / Cursor container typically has no GPU Kit binaries.
- Override host repo path with `SPARK_HOST_REPO_ROOT` / user with
  `SPARK_HOST_USER` when needed. Opt into container Isaac with
  `SPARK_ALLOW_CONTAINER_ISAAC=1` only when Kit is actually mounted.
- Do not suppress warnings to make tests look green. Resolve Isaac / URDF /
  Python warnings at the source.
- Before each monitored Isaac or long pytest cycle, kill leftover background
  log streamers (`tail -F` of `/tmp/*smoke*`, `/tmp/gui_*`, `/tmp/headless_*`,
  `assets/logs/isaac_host/latest*.log`, and agent DEC/RESULT streamers).
- Until Phase 7 GUI smoke exists, use `./scripts/run_verification.sh ci` for
  remote-equivalent gates and the same script's `spark` mode for host unit/GPU
  gates. After Phase 7 acceptance, never push Isaac-path changes until GUI
  smoke exits 0; do not bypass with `SPARK_RUN_ISAAC_GUI_SMOKE=0`.
- If Ruff is missing in the Isaac ROS / Cursor container, run
  `./scripts/ensure_container_dev_tools.sh` (or let `run_verification.sh`
  bootstrap it). Install only lightweight `dev` tools there; never install
  cuRobo/CUDA/Isaac Kit just for lint.
- Never claim sub-millimeter real-world accuracy without hardware evidence.
  Simulation thresholds are sim metrics only.
- Hardware motion requires `ENABLE_MYCOBOT_HARDWARE_TESTS=1`. Default tests and
  launches are dry-run only.
- After primary code pushes, finish `STATUS.md`, `CHANGES.md`, and
  `docs/last_prompt.md`, then run `./scripts/git_secondary_docs_push.sh` and
  stop editing those three files in that turn.
